The article discusses President Donald J. Trump's foreign policy, which emphasizes direct engagement with the world and American leadership based on shared security interests with allies. The policy, called "Principled Realism," aims to act in America's national interest and in accordance with its values. The article highlights several key aspects of the policy, including a strong stance against North Korean provocations, efforts to curb Iran's destabilizing activities, standing up for the Venezuelan people against tyranny, defeating ISIS and fighting terrorism globally, strengthening partnerships in the Middle East, and renewing the NATO alliance. The President has been actively working with international partners to achieve these goals.